metadata.title: Where Europeans Consider Corruption Widespread
metadata.description: Share of EU-28 respondents considering corruption widespread in 2017
metadata.main_insight: There is a significant difference in the perception of corruption across EU countries, with Greece having the highest percentage of respondents considering it widespread and Finland the lowest.

datafacts.annotation: Greece has highest Perception of Corruption
datafacts.reason: Greece has the highest Perception of Corruption at 96.0

datafacts.annotation: Finland has lowest Perception of Corruption
datafacts.reason: Finland has the lowest Perception of Corruption at 21.0

datafacts.annotation: Gap between highest and lowest is 75.0
datafacts.reason: The difference between the highest value (96.0) and lowest value (21.0) is 75.0
The average Perception of Corruption across all Country values is 70.2

datafacts.annotation: Perception of Corruption varies significantly across Country
datafacts.reason: The Perception of Corruption shows considerable variation across different Country values, with a range of 75.0
